	<div id="tribute-data">
	  <!-- Achievements and other details of the person -->
	  <h1 class="title-KR">
	    About the Legend
	  </h1>
	
	
	<p>
	
	
	<ul style="list-style-type:square;">
	  <li> <b>Full Name:</b> Keanu Charles Reeves </li>
	  <li> <b>Born:</b> September 2, 1964 </li>
	  <li> <b>Birth city:</b> Beirut, Lebanon </li>
	  <li> <b>Nationality:</b> Canadian </li>
	  <li> <b>Parents:</b> Patricia Taylor (English originating form Essex)
           <br> Samuel Nowlin Reeves Jr. (American from Hawaii with Chinese, English, Irish
            and Portuguese descent)</li><br>
	  <li> <b>The Beginning:</b> Reeves started acting in theatre and in a variety of 
	       television series before landing his role in <i>The Matrix</i>.
		   As a teenager with dyslexia, he had trouble reading and as a consequence of this,
		   he wasn't a very good student. He was talented in other areas though. Actually, Keanu
		   was a very skilled ice hockey goalkeeper at De La Salle College and gained apirations
		   to become a professional ice hockey player for the Canadian Olympic team. At 15, he 
		   switched gears and decided to become an actor. As he pursued his dreams as an actor,
		   he attended Avondale Secondary Alternative School. Shortly after he turned 17, he 
		   dropped out of high school, obtained a green card through his American stepfather
		   and headed to Los Angeles.</li> <br>
	  <li> <b>Early career:</b> Reeves worked for the Canadian Broadcasting Corporation youth
		   television program <i>Going Great</i> in 1984. Then he played as <i>Mercutio</i> in
		   a theatre production of <i>Romeo and Juliet</i> at the Leah Posluns Theatre in New
		   York, Ontario. Starting in 1986, he made several appearances in television films with
		   titles from <i>Brotherhood of Justice</i>, <i>Act of Vengeance</i>, <i>Youngblood</i>
		   ,and <i> River's Edge</i>.</li><br>
	 <li> <b>Breaking ground:</b> Reeves broke ground when he snatched an opportunity to work
			next to Patrick Swayze, Lori Petty, and Gary Busey in the action movie <i>Point Break</i>.
			On the side, the start developed an interest in music and formed an alternative rock 
			group called, "Dogstar" in 1991 and played the bass guitar. One year later, he starred
			alongside famous actors such as Gary Oldman, Winona Ryder and Anthony Hopkins in the film
			<i>Bram Stoker's Dracula</i>. The movie grossed a total of $215.8 million around the world.
			Although the film was successful, Reeves was stricly criticised because he was required to
			speak with an English accent. He soon took an interest in science fiction roles, and played
			as a researched in <i>Chain Reaction</i>. The film did not do so well as it was rated 16%
			by Rotten Tomatoes.</li><br>
	  <li> <b>Limelight:</b> In 1999, Keanu Reeves played the role of "Neo" in the award winning franche
			<b>The Matrix</b>. The cast trained for months through intense training in preparation for
			the fight scenes. The film was considered to be one of the best science fictions of all time.
			Academy Awards endowed the film for Best Film Editing, Best Sound Editing, Best Visual Effects,
			and Best Sound. Reeves did not stop here and continued to star in <i>Constantine</i> which 
			grossed $230 million internationally from a $100 million budget in 2005.</li><br>
	  <li> <b>The Downturn:</b> The limelight was not meant to shine on Reeves forever and it faded away.
			Reeves then worked in a crime thriller film <i>Street Kings</i> which grossed a moderated $66
			million worldwide and was criticised as "fundamentally blank and uninteresting" by <i>The
			Guardian</i>. He then starred in several romantic comedy films which received amicable reviews.
			In 2013, he debut as a director in the martial arts film <i>Man of Tai Chi</i> which grossed
			only $5.5 million worldwide from a total budget of $25 million. </li><br>
	  <li> <b>The Revival:</b> Reeves' career bounced back in 2014 when he played the iconic role in the 
			action thriller <i>John Wick</i> directed by Chad Stahelski. Reeves and Stahelski worked closely
			together to develop the storyline. Reeves stated, "We all agreed on the potential of the project.
			 I love the role, but you want the whole story, the whole ensemble to come to life." <i>The
			 Hollywood Report</i> was so impressed by Reeves' performance and the director's "confident,
			 muscular action debut." The film grossed $86 million worldwide which lead to the production of
			 <i>John Wick: Chapter 2</i> grossing $171.5 million worldwide. The third installment of the
			 series <i>John Wick: Chapter 3</i> followed the same light and grossed $171 million in the usemap
			 and more than $155 million worldwide. </li><br>
	  <li> <b>Media Talk:</b> Lev Grossman called Keanu Reeves "Hollywood's ultimate introvert" in a 2005 
			article for <i>Time</i> magazine. Reeves was described by others as charming, workaholic and
			"excruciatingly shy." The public has dubbed him as the "Internet's boyfriend" and became an icon
			when he appeared at the E3 2019 debut for the game <i>Cyberpunk 2077</i>.</li><br>
	  
	  
	</p>
